                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-12 - Gorden Updates posted to Game Play forum</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <p><span class="newstext">Gordon made several posts on the Gameplay forum today,
here is a summary:
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/061142.html"><b>New
    Q&amp;A Forum</b></a><br>
    Hello all,
    <p>We have added a Quality Assurance forum to the forum list to allow players
    to chat directly with the Test team concerning bugs in the game. Both Ester
    and &quot;Hobart&quot; will be posting in the forum, and I imagine that they will
    be posting an intro soon.
    <p>As a reminder, the forum there to assist the Test team with the
    documentation of bugs in game. We will continue to post there as long as the
    forum serves its purpose. I ask for everyones assistance in keeping it
    flame-free. If it turns into Gameplay, we will scrap the idea until we have
    the boards shifted over to allow only active subscribers the ability to
    post.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/061133.html"><b>Karana
    Split</b></a><br>
    We have decided to do a secondary split on Karana, moving another batch of
    players off to Terris-Thule. /Movelog registration will open Friday around
    7pm and will remain open for 24 hours.
    <p>Please check the patch message for details. The message should be up
    shortly.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/061063.html"><b>Soloing</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: refer to the link, long
    post]</i></font>
    <p>As I have mentioned before, there are classes that can solo in certain
    situations. However if you are looking for a server setup where anyone can
    solo for experience, at any time, and in any situation, thats not something
    that we will see in EverQuest. Soloing requires reduced dependence on other
    classes, so giving everyone the ability to solo means that we would have to
    eliminate class dependency.I am sure that it is a valid niche, and I am sure
    that other game companies will make games to fill that niche, however we
    prefer to produce games that encourage interaction.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/061055.html"><b>Superior
    Healing</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: But ACK.. that means
    paladins are left out??? Thats the main thing I do nowadays.. HEAL. And
    casters are welcome to the damage I deal out. So can paladins get superior
    heal at 53 as well, please?]</i></font>
    <p>This is not a change that we would consider making at this point. Druids
    and shaman are supposed to be better healers than Paladins, since paladins
    have such an advantage in the melee and &quot;tanking&quot; areas.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060999.html"><b>Monk
    Damage</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: I think Abashi stated,
    pre-Kunark, it was a 15% boost in damage over a comparably equipped and
    leveled warrior]</i></font>
    <p>Actually, the only time that I believe I made any statement in the form
    of a percentage was when we put in the innate haste for monk hand speeds. As
    I recall, the statement was something along the lines of High level monks
    should now do roughly 15% more damage. I do not believe I ever made a
    statement comparing them to a similarly equipped warrior, other than to
    state that they should generally do more damage. Correct me if I am wrong.
    <p>That said, monks are still the best toe-to-toe melee damage dealer, which
    is right where they are supposed to be. Monks rock.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060532.html"><b>Band
    of Eternal Flame</b></a><br>
    You would be in a better position to answer if it is still dropping than I. I
    generally do not go for answering questions of this nature unless the item
    was so common or in for so long that it had become &quot;expected&quot;.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/058408-2.html"><b>Jolt
    Improvements</b></a><br>
    It was a 1 second improvement, or roughly a 30% improvement in casting time.
    I would call that &quot;real&quot;. Perhaps the misunderstanding is the typical
    one on this board, that an enhancement is &quot;useless&quot; unless it
    unbalances the class. Of course since we try not to make changes that do
    that, we are in a bit of a catch-22.
    <p>We are considering upping damage output for rangers though.</p>
  </li>
</ul>
</span>

</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: EverQuest Announcments -  </font> <a href=http://www.everquest.com </a> www.everquest.com </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-12 - Gorden is Back and Posting!</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <p><span class="newstext">Gorden is back from the Gathering and posting, here is
a summary:</span></p>
<span class="newstext">
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060784.html"><b>Welcome
    Back Gordon!</b></a><br>
    <br>
    Hello all,<br>
    Weve all returned from EQ Gathering III in sunny (and hot) Las Vegas. The
    event went *very* well and Id like to extend thanks to all of those who
    attended. I imagine that those who didnt go will be able to view reports
    being given by various web sites, many of whom were in attendance.
    <p>Several events took place at the gathering, including a Trivia Contest
    and the &quot;RealLife Quest&quot;, an EQ oriented scavenger hunt. Kudos
    goes to one of the groups of Rangers for winning the Trivia Contest, and to
    a team from Povar who took the &quot;RealLife Quest&quot; by gathering
    nearly 80 items found regularly within the game. One of the more creative
    items turned in was a real human tooth submitted to represent the
    &quot;Giant Elephant Tusk&quot; in the scavenger hunt.
    <p>Overall, the Team here at Verant enjoyed the chance to meet the players
    and discuss the issues at hand. I personally had the chance to speak with
    several hundred people, quite a few here from the boards, and found the
    whole experience very positive and refreshing. We definitely look forward to
    going to the next one.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060819.html"><b>On
    Dwarf Paladins</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: According to EQ lore.
    Brell created many things. Among them are the so called good races such as
    Dwarves and Gnomes. However he also created the Splitpaw Gnolls, Runnyeye
    Goblins and also created those elementals who run amuk in Tox forest killing
    Erudites.]</i></font><br>
    Well, Teerog covered it pretty well. Its certainly a valid way to look at
    everything. One question I would like to ask however, who said Brell created
    the Gnolls and Goblins? Now before someone follows up, I invite you to read
    the deity description when creating a dwarven paladin *closely*.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060814.html"><b>Angry
    Clerics</b></a><br>
    Ive read the posts, and havent found the issue that you cite to be any more
    pronounced than for any other class. As most people cite clerics as one of
    the most desirable group members, I doubt that theyll be going anywhere
    soon. There will always be some people who do not enjoy the life of a cleric
    and they will move on.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060797.html"><b>Forum
    Posts and IP Tracking</b></a><br>
    Thanks for the heads-up. The work to restrict posting on these boards for
    anyone but active EQ subscribers is finally moving forward, and I imagine
    that well see it in a couple of weeks. Following that change, well begin
    strictly moderating the boards.
    <p>As it is now, about all we can do is delete the wholly offensive posts
    and cross-reference IP addresses with those used to log into the game. Were
    committed for these boards to once again be a useful tool. Those who have
    nothing better to do than issue flames and personal attacks can move on.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060796.html"><b>More
    on the Boards</b></a><br>
    I believe the concern is that if we limit it to active subscribers, were
    giving people who are trying to hack accounts real station names. Weve
    actually got that problem solved. The implementation will link the Stations
    authentication servers into our (EQs) login database. Instead of displaying
    the Station name, well display the Chat Handle. Being one company now
    certainly has its advantages
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060781.html"><b>Necklace
    of Superiority</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: Been trying to get
    information for days...Does anyone know if necklace of superiority is still
    dropping even rarely? Heard it drops in howling stones, heard it drops
    rarely or not at all in Dalnir]</i></font>
    <p>This item was originally dropping off of the wrong creature. It has been
    moved to a new location in game.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060697.html"><b>Really
    Long Bug List</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:1)The Random Faction hit
    bug in Kunark is still around. Mobs are still charging at people from
    rediculous distances. The odd thing is, if you stun a mob and run away with
    sow, it will not follow you, yet if a mob is aggro on you in some different
    case, it can charge at you from the other side of the zone. The aggro list
    is bugged still.]</i></font>
    <p>These arent random, and have to do with the propagation of the hate list.
    If you cast a beneficial spell upon someone who is on a hatelist, you are
    also added to that hatelist, and will receive a faction adjustment when that
    creature is finally killed. As for this and the pursuit issue that youve
    outlined, weve labeled these issues as &quot;features&quot; associated with
    the large Kunark zones.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:2)The boat is going in
    the wrong direction in OOT. When you are heading east your sense heading
    says west and vice versa]</i></font>
    <p>Its a known issue, and cant be fixed without rebuilding the zone, tying
    up level-designers for man-months. Given that, weve waived this bug.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:3)Mobs in Qeynos Hills
    literally teleport. Anyone who has hunted Tovax Vmar knows exactly what I
    mean. Test it yourself with a low level character...when he starts to run,
    he vanishes.]</i></font>
    <p>The &quot;Start to flee and disappear&quot; teleport bug was fixed
    several months ago. If you are certain that it has resurfaced, please let me
    know.]
    <p>&nbsp;
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:4)When a PC goes LD,
    the pet becomes rogue. If the party is fighting a mob and the &quot;rogue
    pet&quot; kills the mob, no one is awarded xp and the fallen monsters body
    vanishes.]</i></font>
    <p>The pet isnt completely rogue, but it does become the &quot;pet of an NPC&quot;,
    presenting the issue that youve described. This is a known issue, works as
    designed, and weve no short term plans to make changes to these mechanics.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:5)Enchanter Illusions
    do not show size correctly. As a gnome, all my illusions show me gnome
    sized, even ogres. This would be deadly in PVP since enchanters can no
    longer cast mez in cities.]</i></font>
    <p>Were aware about the size issue. The only people who see you as your
    original height are the ones that are zoning as you cast the spell. This
    issue cannot be fixed due to the way height changes are reported to clients.
    The issue has been waived.As for not being able to cast Mez in cities, I
    dont know what you are refering to.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:6)Sometimes illusions
    wont break, and one is forced to stay in a particular form until one zones
    or logs.]</i></font>
    <p>Ive had this happen to me a couple of times, but we dont have a way to
    reproduce it. Once we can find a way to reproduce it we should be able to
    make some progress on it.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:7)Standing too close
    to a wall makes you invisible to players zoning in. You have to relog to
    clear it.]</i></font>
    <p>I dont think that this is attributable to being next to a wall, but
    rather is associated with packetloss issues. The system only updates who is
    visible or not when there is a change in status. When zoning in, for some
    reason the visibility flag isnt set properly. You would be able to see them
    if they were to cast invisibility on themselves then cancel it, but would
    otherwise have to log/zone out and back in. This is another issue where a
    reproduction method is lacking, and where we might be able to take some
    action if we can find out what is causing it. Its rather intermittent, but
    Ill ask Ester the Tester to take a look.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:8)Many times if you
    are hit while zoning, you can pop up into the same zone you were zoning
    from, with full health, at usually loc 0,0. I have had this happen to me in
    Mistmoore and Crushbone multiple times.]</i></font>
    <p>Youre actually put back at the last save-point. Its a feature to handle
    cases where you are killed between the time that your client thinks you
    start zoning and the time that the zoneserver gets the message that you are
    zoning. Its one of the downsides of internet latency. The &quot;pop back at
    savepoint&quot; is a second chance to get out of the zone. The other option,
    and some will remember when this was in, was to leave your dead corpse
    behind the zoneline.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:9)Stronger members of
    the &quot;Slow&quot; line of spells are overwritten by weaker ones. Not sure
    if this is a bug, but all the other spells seem to follow the &quot;Stronger
    Replaces Weaker&quot; trend.]</i></font>
    <p>Yes, its a bug. We hope to make some headway in fixing it soon.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:10)Clipping Plane
    still not set to full value in zones. This can be seen when it was raining
    in the Old World and Kunark.]</i></font>
    <p>Brad explained this as a &quot;feeling&quot; that the players were
    getting when rain or fog was stopping, that it would momentarily extend
    sight beyond the distance where it was normally available with the max
    distance set on the clipping plane. Were still looking into whether that
    additional distance is actually viewable or not.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:11)In Dalnir, the Kly
    Imprecator on the 2nd floor, or anything that spawns in his spot, can pop up
    through the ceiling and shortly despawn after that. ]</i></font>
    <p>Im not familiar with this NPC popping through the ceiling, but the
    despawn is intended. Ill forward this to the Test Team.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:12)When Someone
    invites you into a group, if you dont reject their offer you are bugged
    until you camp. You cant join another group until you camp and come back. ]</i></font>
    <p>Ive seen this one before, Ill ask testing to make sure that its on the
    list.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:13)In Blackburrow,
    near the elite ledge, if you stand directly on top of the pile of bones,
    npcs cant hit you. You can nuke away with no risk of retaliation (the
    pathing prevents them from getting at you).]</i></font>
    <p>Thanks for the note. Ill send it to Testing. Do you have a /loc?
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:14)In Highkeep, if you
    walk up the steps to the guy who gives the bloody shank quest, then hop over
    on the platform and then hop once more to another ledge, you can stand there
    and nuke the guards and theyll do nothing but stand there and take it.]</i></font>
    <p>I thought we took care of all of the issues in Highkeep about 2 patches
    ago. Have a /loc?
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:15)If one equips a
    ranged slot after equipping a melee slot, it seems like one melees with the
    ranged weapon. Eat my preserved Split Paw Eye!!!]</i></font>
    <p>Ive never seen this problem. Can you be more specific as to the repro
    steps?
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:16)Some emotes that
    have to decide a players sex (to instert &quot;him&quot; or &quot;her&quot;
    into the sentence insert wacked characters instead. &quot;Soandso pants and
    drools. Something must have gotten excited!&quot;]</i></font>
    <p>Thanks, its in our database.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:17)If you disband your
    group while a group member(s) is zoning/LD, that zoning/LD group member(s)
    can become &quot;bugged&quot; and then disbanding and/or regrouping becomes
    impossible.]</i></font>
    <p>The only incarnation of something like this that Ive seen is where one
    group member zones, goes LD while zoning, and the *remaining* group members
    cant regroup or disband. Is this that you are speaking of?
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:18)Most frequently in
    newbie zones, a mob will appear to be floating a few feet above the ground.
    This is invariably 2 mobs attempting to occupy the same space in the game,
    so if you attack this &quot;floating mob&quot;, it moves, they both drop to
    the ground, and more often than not, you end up with 2 on you.]</i></font>
    <p>Its a known issue created by static (non-moving) spawns occuring at the
    same location. It typically happens in Newbie zones because they have a very
    high concentration of critters in a smaller area. This could probably be
    fixed but would take quite a while to do. As such, higher priority things
    usually take precedence. Thankfully newbies learn pretty quickly that
    &quot;Floating creatures&quot; = &quot;More than one&quot;.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:19)When a person zones
    into someplace, he/she might receive a battle message: You have entered
    Black Burrow. You hit a Gnoll Brewer for 20 points of damage. A Gnoll Brewer
    dies.]</i></font>
    <p>Actually the message is that you miss, but they die anyway Its a known
    bug, an inappropriate message. We dont have a way to reproduce this, and
    since it doesnt affect gameplay, it has been low priority.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:20)When cleric NPCs
    cast a cetain spell it says: &quot;XXXX feels the eyes of the gods watching
    them.&quot; Them should be him or her.]</i></font>
    <p>Your grammar is correct. However, spell-effect messages do not have the
    ability to place a variable that goes through a process to determine gender.
    This might be an nice enhancement some day.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:21)There is a thread
    about multiple Graphical Bugs with Erudites, Gnomes, and Halflings. All of
    those issues deal with equipping certain armor pieces. These should be
    looked into as well.]</i></font>
    <p>These are known problems, but a fix doesnt appear to be forthcoming in
    the near future due to download size. Well keep the issue open in the
    meantime.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:22)Various Plane of
    Sky Quest Pieces have Vanished from Players inventory !!!]</i></font>
    <p>Some of the quests have been changed over time. If the item currently
    held no longer has a use, it could very well have disappeared.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:23)When a quest or
    trade skill recipe calls for multiple stackable items, they cannot be
    stacked. This is something that most people would reasonably expect to be
    able to do.]</i></font>
    <p>This issue is known, and we have no plans to change it in the short term.
    Please seperate your items into single stacks before submitting them.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:24)The zone-in point
    when going from Qeynos Hills to West Karana is right on top of the zone line
    for going from West Karana to Qeynos Hills. ]</i></font>
    <p>Known issue. Its on our current active project list.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:25)On occaision, both
    boats from Qeynos to Erudin will overlap. Any player on the boat(s) at the
    time of overlap/separation will take upwards of 100points of damage. This is
    an inconvenience for higher level characters, but for newbies/lowbies, it
    can be fatal.]</i></font>
    <p>This is a pain. Current technology doesnt allow it to be fixed. If this
    occurs, please /petition in game for transport and resurrection if needbe.
    Just be sure that you /report the evidence.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:26) [Spoiler Text
    removed.]]</i></font>
    <p>This is not a bug.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:27)The folded sheet of
    metal made by smithing apparently is without application. No one knows of
    any recipe that uses it.]</i></font>
    <p>True. This is not a bug. The folded sheet was an item that was listed as
    makeable but never was. It is makable now, so that bug is fixed. The fact
    that there isnt *yet* a recipe for it just leaves something for future
    expansion.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:28)When travelling
    between Freeport and Butcherblock, the boat sometimes docks at the islands
    too close--the dock and sometimes the NPC will appear on the deck of the
    ship. This isnt a problem unless youre with someone who has bad faction. Its
    an instant KOS if the player happens to be standing on the wrong side of the
    boat.]</i></font>
    <p>Players KOS to critters at the end of a dock probably shouldnt be hanging
    out that close to the edge You arent totally safe on the boat.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:29)2: boat issue; I
    was on boat from Erudin to Qeynos when all of a sudden there was a Plague
    Shark on deck with me, talk about jumping out of your skivies]</i></font>
    <p>It can happen if the two paths cross. Its not a bug. You arent totally
    safe on the boat.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:30)Unrest. Standing in
    the open courtyard just before the tunnel to the zone, I was attacked by 4
    invisible monsters. My party members watched as I turned and vainly tried to
    find the attackers. No one was able to target anything hitting me, and no
    one could see any attackers. There was no tree by me that the mob was hiding
    in, no overhang, no tunnel underneath.]</i></font>
    <p>Being attacked by unseen creatures usually means that they are under the
    world. We correct &quot;NPC under the world&quot; problems quite regularly.
    If anyone has specific repro steps for this problem, wed love to hear them.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:31) In Unrest if you
    are fighting the Undead Knight, the Barkeep and Lord can hit you through the
    floor as they are in the room below.]</i></font>
    <p>This just happens sometimes. NPCs hitting through walls, doors, ceilings,
    etc., is not a bug.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:32)Today in Tox forest
    with my newbie cleric while fighting Elial Brook... group partner got exp
    and I didnt cause I was feared at the time. (were both the same level and we
    both did damage to him, just that I was feared when Elial died).]</i></font>
    <p>Players who are feared at the time of the kill will not get experience.
    Not a bug.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:33)if a NPC fears you,
    after you regain control of yourself you cant left click on anything for
    aproximately 2 minutes. Right click still works but that does no good
    because you cant cast any spells or sit or anything. I noticed this in
    Nektulos Forest killing the shadow men. I have also talked to a few other
    people that have noticed it in other places from other types of NPCs. This
    bug really needs to be fixed becuase people could very easily die from it.]</i></font>
    <p>Its on the list. No ETR.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:34)this Necro spell is
    still broken. It has never worked since it came out with Kunark.]</i></font>
    <p>I assume you mean the &quot;Track Corpse&quot; spell since you didnt
    mention it, but its the only one I know of that is broken. Known issue,
    thanks, no ETR.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:35)Necro COB Lich Line
    of spells will sometimes be uncancelable even though the icon is gone.]</i></font>
    <p>This is the same as #6. See above.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:36)Mobs will get
    caught in an aggro loop Continually saying soandso will not evade them but
    unable to get to soandso.]</i></font>
    <p>Specific NPCs and conditions are needed.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:37)The tinkering
    recipe for the Thermal Cloak calls for a Tattered Gnomish Clock, which does
    not exist in game...at least NO ONE on any of the servers I play on has ever
    seen one.]</i></font>
    <p>The Thermal Cloak is not craftable per hte reasons you mention. Ill see
    if we can get this fixed.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:38)If your account is
    Kunark-enabled, and you log in on a machine that does not have Kunark
    installed on it, and were camped on or otherwise attempt to travel to Kunark,
    you get thrown into an endless loop of falling for 32000 HP. Over and over
    and over...]</i></font>
    <p>First, you will only fall for 10K. Secondly, you will only fall for 10K
    over and over if also bound in a Kunark zone which isnt installed on the
    machine from which you are logged in. Not a bug. Do not attempt to log in
    characters located in Kunark on machines that dont have the files installed.
    If you do, dont let yourself fall for 10K over and over again. Quit out
    until you are able to get back to another machine.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:39)There are several
    doors in the game that wont open. Two I can think of: In BlackBurrow near
    the snake pit, and in AlAknon, in the guardhouse near the entrance. ]</i></font>
    <p>Doors that wont open are not bugs.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:40)A (very) minor one:
    When you have all inventory slots full, and try to right-click to pick up a
    stackable item, the game responds that you dont have room, even if you have
    a stack of that item that is not yet full.]</i></font>
    <p>Known and annoying problem. Its on the list.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:41)The sharks at the
    Erudin docks like to fly around. I have also seen this once on the boat from
    Erudin to Qeynos. Probably related: the sentinels in Erudin sometimes use
    the swimming animation when on dry land.]</i></font>
    <p>Known issue, pathing around water is awful, espicially in the older zones
    before some new pathing technology was implemented. Wed probably like to fix
    this at some point.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:42)The lvl 20 mage
    spell Shield of Flame has the worng spell icon color. It displayed yellow
    (self only) when it should be red since it is a one target buff. (Other like
    shields are all red)]</i></font>
    <p>Thanks for the note.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:43)When you are in
    Cazic dungeon, and approach the zone out, the hallway turns to the right. As
    soon as you zone, the hallway actually turns to the left. Very confusing,
    and caused me to zone back in the first few times.]</i></font>
    <p>This confused me too. Cant be fixed without the zone being rebuilt, much
    like the OOT issue. Though this would take less time to fix, theres still
    the issue of the download. For these reasons this issue is waived.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:44)emote/casting
    messages. &quot; rises from the dead&quot;. An obvious typo,, as it should
    be &quot;s pet&quot; instead of &quot;&quot; or some correct variation.]</i></font>
    <p>We might be able to change this in this fashion. We would not, however,
    be able to get it to place the pets actual name as part of the spell effect.
    Ill ask the guys if they can stick a &quot;s pet&quot; in the string.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:45)In the enchanter
    quest for the Incandescent Wand, Sultin in the Temple of Sol Ro tells you to
    go to &quot;Esmirella&quot; in the North Karana gypsy camp. The NPCs actual
    name is &quot;Ezmirella&quot;.]</i></font>
    <p>Maybe he cant spell? Seriously though, thanks for the note.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post:46)For some reason a
    Large Sewing Kit can hold larger items in it than a backpack or large Box
    can...]</i></font>
    <p>Weve decided not to change this at this time since doing so would cause
    those with larger items in them at the time to lose those items. In the
    meantime, the chance of hitting &quot;Combine&quot; by accident is just
    payment for exploiting the kit.Thanks for your notes. Ill refer Ester the
    Tester to the thread
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060630.html"><b>Buff
    Lengths</b></a><br>
    The duration of the buffs mentioned here hasnt changed. If it had, Im sure
    that the people who parse the spell file would have noticed and that thered
    be no question I imagine that some might be getting the &quot;feeling&quot;
    that the buffs are wearing off sooner since Kunark launched, since there is
    far more to keep a group busy. The phrase &quot;time flies when youre having
    fun&quot; certainly applies.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060612.html"><b>Language
