    my target..crashes...fataly...]</i></font>
    <p>Are you sure that its crashing, or does it just lock up? If its the
    latter, you can probably hit ALT-TAB once to shift the focus back to the EQ
    Client. CTRL-ESC shifts focus to the Windows Task Bar.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060605.html"><b>Critters</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: they can be level 1 and
    have no exp for all i care but it would be neat to see rabbits and cows and
    chickens running around certain zones like the fronteer mountians while
    camping giants or south karana... ]</i></font>
    <p>Something along these lines would be nice to see. However, we do have to
    keep system requirements in mind. Each thing of this nature would require
    that additional polygons be rendered, and additional textures loaded into
    the video card. We could limit the polys by replacing existing NPCs with
    these &quot;environment builders&quot; I suppose, but Im guessing that many
    wouldnt like that idea.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060346.html"><b>Hacking
    and Email Scams</b></a><br>
    <font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: May 31st I got an email
    from the Sony Station saying that I had requested for my password to be
    changed. I had not asked for this to happen so I decided not to return the
    email for a new password]</i></font>
    <p>If you could, please forward me (gwrinn@verant.com) a copy of the email
    that you received, as an attachment, so that the headers remain intact. The
    Station doesnt send out email asking people to change their passwords, much
    less asking them to email their password selection back. Theres a very good
    chance that this is some sort of scam.
    <p>The vast majority of hacking complaints can be traced back to one of the
    following things:
    <p>1. Account information given to friends or guildmates who later steal the
    account.<br>
    2. Other family members playing on the same account.<br>
    3. Sold accounts (since the original owner can call back at any time to get
    the account back).
    <p>As for your email address being changed, most likely the person who
    somehow obtained your login information changed the email address once they
    were able to log in. This was probably to be sure that your attempts to get
    the account back via the &quot;I forgot my password&quot; routine would
    fail.
    <p><font color="#072876"><i>[Quote from original post: He informed me that
    they probably, accidentaly, blocked my account.]</i></font>
    <p>I havent heard of any case of us accidentally blocking an account before.
    They should only be &quot;blocked&quot; if billing fails, if the subscriber
    is under 13 years of age, or if the station account is terminated for some
    reason.
    <p>Id be interested in hearing any other information that you can provide.
    We do not have any untraceable vulnerabilities in our system or procedures
    that would allow for accounts to be stolen.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060131.html"><b>Looting
    on Rallos Zek</b></a><br>
    <p>Ive given as straight of an answer as I can at this time. We do not have
    any plans at this time to change loot rules on Rallos Zek in any significant
    manner, nor do we plan on moving people there to the Team servers. The need
    for coin-only and the subsequent change to that looting methodology was
    planned only for the Team servers, with Rallos remaining as is. Rallos Zeks
    narrower level range (+/- 4 levels as opposed to +/- 8) allows item loot to
    remain in the environment. Were not prepared to entirely give up on the idea
    at this point.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/060098.html"><b>Poison
    Making</b></a><br>
