    doesnt have files for t he Overthere installed. Thats the only situation
    that would result it you appearing to be in south Qeynos.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/059602.html"><b>Language
    and Filters</b></a><br>
    <p>Actually that quote was in regards to obscenities here on the boards,
    particularly that which is done to intentionally bypass the obscenity
    filter. In game however, though the filter is provided to allow people the
    opportunity to avoid the occasional and accidental obscenity, no one should
    be subjected to pure obscenity for obscenitys sake. The existance of the
    filter is not meant to be a license to freely shout profanity across a zone.
    The argument that &quot;they can /ignore&quot; or &quot;they can turn the
    filter on&quot; is somewhat analogous to the real life argument that anyone
    should be able to run around unclothed in public on the basis that other
    people have the option to &quot;just dont look&quot;.
    <p>EverQuest is very often a family game, with other family members often
    looking on or playing along on their own computers. Well pursue keeping the
    environment suitable for that purpose.
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/055873.html"><b>Clipping
    Planes</b></a><br>
    We dont have any further information to extend at this time. Well be sure to
    update you as soon as we have some news.</li>
